{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "23", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "06", "M": "56", "S": "14"}}, "news": [{"title": "Buildings in Indore given 15 days to ensure compliance with fire safety norms", "para": "Indore district administration has issued a 15-day ultimatum to G+3 and multi-storey buildings to comply with fire safety norms. Special teams will inspect buildings for operational fire extinguishers, sprinklers, and clear emergency exits. Non-compliant structures face punitive action, including licence cancellation and demolition of illegal expansions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/indore-sets-15-day-deadline-for-fire-safety-compliance-in-buildings/129741691?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-39270/129741691.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Affordable flats at five sites for urban poor: Odisha minister", "para": "Odisha is undertaking five major affordable housing projects in Bhubaneswar, Cuttack, and Rourkela through public-private partnerships. These initiatives, following the Housing for All (Urban) policy, will deliver over 5,000 dwelling units for economically weaker and lower-income groups, addressing the growing demand for low-cost housing in urban areas.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/odisha-government-launches-affordable-housing-projects-for-urban-poor/129741676?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-68526/129741676.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Existing land use survey drags, Nagpur development plan in doldrums", "para": "Nagpur's development plan faces significant delays as the Existing Land Use survey remains incomplete in over half of the expanded municipal areas. The Nagpur Municipal Corporation is struggling to reconcile land-use details from the Nagpur Improvement Trust, impacting the plan's adherence to statutory timelines. The municipal commissioner has set a new deadline of May 31 for completing the survey.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/existing-land-use-survey-drags-nagpur-development-plan-in-doldrums/129741665?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-92038/129741665.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}